<HEADLINE> Tanzania Calls for Clean Production Methods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian government has
urged industrial enterprises in the country to adopt cleaner
production techniques and technologies to achieve sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a cleaner production financing workshop held in Dar
es Salaam Wednesday, the Minister of State in the Vice-President's
Office Edward Lowasa said industrial enterprises must adopt
strategies that can help avoid costly environmental problems so as
to achieve economic growth and protect environment at the same
time.
</P>
<P>
He called upon Tanzanian industrialists, technical experts,
financial institutions and law enforcers to work together in order
to achieve common objectives on environment.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania has recently been chosen by United Nations
Environment Program (UNEP) to participate in a pilot project on
cleaner production financing mechanisms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
