<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece, France Sign Agreement on Illegal Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Greece and France signed here
Wednesday an agreement providing for the readmission of illegal
immigrants.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Greece's Secretary-General for
European Union (EU) Affairs Stelios Perrakis and France's Charge D
' affairs in Athens Michel Vandepoorter, according to a statement
from the Greek Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is part of the bilateral framework of cooperation
governed by the Schengen treaty and is the second Greece has
signed with another EU member state.
</P>
<P>
Greece is to become a full member of the Schengen treaty on
January 1, 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
