<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Gets Rid of  Y2K Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's National
Technical Committee announced Wednesday that Ethiopia is absolved
from Y2K problem.
</P>
<P>
Critical units like banks, telecommunications, electric power
plants, airlines, the Ministry of Finance, custom authority have
been proved ready when the new millennium comes, the committee
chairman Alemayehu Tesfaye told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Mesfin Lemma, a member of the
National Technical Committee, as saying that Ethiopia was found to
be in a better position in eradicating the millennium bug compared
to other East African countries.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has received financial support from the World Bank in
solving the computer problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
