<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Petroleum Company Punished for Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Revenue
Authority (TRA) has decided to auction over 1.4 million liters of
fuel belonging to a local oil company in order to recover the
taxes evaded by the firm.
</P>
<P>
The decision was one of the measures taken by the authority to
fight tax evasion, said the TRA acting commissioner general Harry
Kitilya Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
TRA has decided to auction the products of Messrs Petrol
Marketing Company in order to recover between 200 and 300 million
Tanzania shillings (250,000 to 375,000 U.S. dollars) which the
company evaded through transit trade of petroleum products.
</P>
</TEXT>
