<HEADLINE> London Stock Ends Lower For 3rd Straight Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 15 (Xinhua) - London stock market ended
sharply lower Wednesday as investors continued to shift cash out
of tech and telecom stocks under the influence of weakness in the
US tech sector.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 finished off 68.3 points, or 1.02 percent, at 6633.
8 as a host of high-tech heavyweights ran into a roadblock
following recent gains.
</P>
<P>
The fall by the UK benchmark on the session meant it now
resided some 138 points below its record high of 6772.1 set on
December 3.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 300, a broader gauge of the pan European mood,
finished down nearly 1 percent at 1480.61.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, a sharp retreat in recent market gains such as tech
services provider PCAP and chip maker PSGS weighed heavily on the
blue-chip CAC 40. The index finished down 0.62 percent at 5530.13,
a loss of 34.34 points.
</P>
<P>
The electronically traded Xetra Dax in Frankfurt bucked the
regional downturn, ending 0.7 percent higher at 6232.75 as sharp
gains in the auto sector offset the drag from slumping telecom
stocks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
