<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Confirms  "Terrorist" Arrests in Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The White House on
Wednesday confirmed that thirteen people suspected of planning
attacks against Americans were arrested in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
"We certainly believe these were members of (Osama) bin Laden's
organization that posed threat to Americans," White House
spokesman Joe Lockhart told reporters. But he declined to discuss
details of the arrest, other than to note that they had been
carried out by the Jordanian government.
</P>
<P>
"We are following closely a number of threats and continue to
be every vigilant on that front," Lockhart added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, In Amman, Jordan, Prime Minister Abdur Ra'
uf Rawabdeh told a parliament session that authorities had
arrested Afghan-trained members of a terrorist group who had tried
to carry out attacks against the state and Jordanian personalities.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the 13 people arrested in Jordan, Middle Eastern
countries had detained more people suspected of planning "
terrorist" attacks, according to a U.S. administration official.
But he declined to comment on the countries where the other
arrests were made.
</P>
<P>
"Some are clearly related to bin Laden, or fairly clearly.
Others are more tenuously but are somehow associated with the
potential for terrorism," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
