<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Ruling Party Refutes Opposition's Claim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's ruling Frelimo
(Mozambique Liberation Front) Party on Wednesday dismissed the
claim by the main opposition party Renamo (Mozambique National
Resistance) that it has won the general elections.
</P>
<P>
At a Maputo press conference, Frelimo general secretary Manuel
Tome said that Renamo was making such claims because in reality it
envisaged defeat.
</P>
<P>
"Faced with a likely defeat, Renamo in despair shouts 'we've
won' in an attempt to confuse the mass media and the international
community," said Tome.
</P>
<P>
This was "just a piece of hysterics" dictated by the failure of
Renamo's attempts to secure victory by fraud, he added.
</P>
<P>
Tome warned that Renamo was "preparing an atmosphere of tension
in which any incident might spark off a chain reaction".
</P>
<P>
He called on all citizens to remain calm and serene, while
waiting for the announcement of the final results.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Renamo spokesperson, Gulamo Jafar, projected that
the opposition Renamo leader Afonso Dhlakama will win between
51.3 and 52.5 percent of the presidential vote, while the
incumbent, Joaquim Chissano with some 47.5 to 48.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tome said by declaring victory in advance Renamo was
"attempting to discredit the real results which only the National
Elections Commission (CNE) is empowered to proclaim".
</P>
<P>
He warned that nobody could accept that a party running in the
elections had the right to proclaim its own figures as the
definitive election results.
</P>
<P>
Tome said that "nobody will permit Renamo, with its lack of a
culture of legality, and its outlaw traditions, to be both player
and referee at the same time".
</P>
<P>
Frelimo, he added, "wishes to make it very clear to all the
Mozambican people, and to the international community, that Renamo
has not won the elections. The only institution that will proclaim
the winner of the election is the CNE".
</P>
<P>
Asked whether Frelimo would accept the final results, if they
did give victory to Renamo, Tome replied "we will accept any
result proclaimed by the CNE in strict compliance with the law".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
