<HEADLINE> China on Additional Instruments Preventing Conflicts in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- It is necessary for the
United Nations Security Council to find new means in order to
prevent and solve conflicts in Africa, China said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the open debate on the situation of Africa by the
Security Council, Chinese Ambassador to the United Nations, Qin
Huasun, said the Security Council dispatched a mission to East
Timor last September to study the situation on the ground which
was received very well by all parties concerned and similarly, the
Security Council can also send missions to the relevant regions of
Africa in order to carry out the study of the situation on the
ground, Qin said,
</P>
<P>
The Security Council should make further efforts in order to
tap the potentials of the existing mechanisms and resources and
the sanctions committee can play a better role in this regard, Qin
said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of African conflicts is very complicated and
therefore, efforts should be made to take care of both the
symptoms and the root causes in a balanced manner, the Ambassador
said.
</P>
<P>
Following the accomplishment of the mandate of the peacekeeping
operations, other relevant organs in the United Nations system
should play their roles properly in the building of peace, and
therefore, the Security Council should further strengthen its
exchanges and cooperation with other relevant organs of the United
Nations, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
