<HEADLINE> Pak Cuts Defense Spending for Development of Poor Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Chief Executive
General Pervaiz Musharraf Wednesday said the defense spending has
been reduced for the development of the poorest regions in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In his televised address on his government's economic package,
Musharraf, who is also Chairman of the Joint Chief of Staff
Committee and Army Chief, said the armed forces have voluntarily
cut down their spending and contributed 7 billion rupees (135
million U.S. dollars) to the small public works in the poorest
regions and rural areas.
</P>
