<HEADLINE> China Presents Angola with Wheel-chairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to Angola
Jiang Yuande Wednesday presented to the Angolan government 200
wheel-chairs, demonstrating its friendship and solidarity towards
the Angolan people.
</P>
<P>
Among the wheel-chairs, 120 will be delivered to the Lwini
Fund, established by the First Lady of Angola Ana Paula dos Santos
for helping vagabond children and the handicapped people, and 80
distributed to other organizations.
</P>
<P>
At the presenting ceremony in Luanda, Jiang said that China
hopes that the Angolan government led by President Jose Eduardo
dos Santos can restore peace and stability in the country as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the development of Sino-Angolan relations over the
past 40 years, Jiang said that "China is a traditional friend of
Angola" and will further develop its fraternal friendship with the
southern African country.
</P>
<P>
At the same function, Angolan Industrial Minister Albina Faria
Assis said that her government hopes to develop the friendly
relations with the compassionate China which has advanced
technology for industrial production.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister of Planning Ana Dias Lourenco and Minister of
Assistance and Social Reintegration Albino Malungo also attended
the ceremony. 
</P>
