<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Casts Largest Copper Bell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Casting of the "China Century
Bell", the largest copper bell in China, started Wednesday night
at a workshop of the Capital Iron and Steel Complex in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The bell, which weighs 50 tons and is 6.8 meters high, will be
used to usher in the new century. It will ring 21 times
simultaneously with four other bells located in Shannxi, Henan,
Shandong and Jiangsu provinces when the new millennium arrives.
</P>
<P>
The bell will be decorated with major historical events in
China over the past century and inscribed with the Chinese
national anthem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
