<HEADLINE> French Police Hunt Suspect of Double Murder on Trains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- French police have launched a
man-hunt against a suspect in two brutal murders of women which
took place on two different night trains within two months.
</P>
<P>
Police have ``half identified'' the suspect, who they described
as a 20-year-old Frenchman of Algerian origin who lived in
Marseille and had served a prison term for rape and violence.
</P>
<P>
The suspect allegedly killed two women -- a British student and
a 36-year-old mother -- on two trains in the night of October 12
and on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses, including train ticket checkers, said the suspect
was on board the train from Limoges to Paris and that from Calais
to Vintimille at the time when the murders took place.
</P>
<P>
The man was traveling without ticket on both trains, said
police.
</P>
<P>
He was suspected to have killed Isabel Peake, a British student,
and Corinne Caillaux, who was traveling with her five-year-old son.
</P>
<P>
Peake was found thrown by the side of the railway line, while
Caillaux was found stabbed by knife in a train restroom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
