<HEADLINE> Goods Train Derails in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Goods and passenger
services between South Africa's Johannesburg and Port Elizabeth
will be delayed for at least three days after 23 wagons of a goods
train derailed in the Eastern Cape Province overnight.
</P>
<P>
The 23 wagons of the 48-wagon train left the track around 10:00
p.m. Tuesday on the rail between Grahamstown and Port Elizabeth,
South African Press Association reported Wednesday. But nobody
was injured and no cargo damaged.
</P>
<P>
However, the tracks were extensively damaged and repair teams
had been sent to the accident site. It was said that the repair
work would not be completed until Saturday or Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Investigators are trying to find the cause of the accident as
it happened on a straight stretch of track. 
</P>
