<HEADLINE> Whites Still to Dominate Top Posts in S. African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's top army
posts will continue to be dominated by whites for the foreseeable
future because of the slow pace of post-apartheid transformation,
Defence Minister Patrick Lekota has said.
</P>
<P>
"The top echelons of the South African National Defense Force
will, for the foreseeable future, be dominated by white officers
of the former South African Defense Force," Lekota said in the
latest issue of Jane's Defence Weekly, a London-based magazine.
</P>
<P>
It is clear that the transformation process -- under which
former African National Congress (ANC) and Pan Africanist Congress
(PAC) guerrillas are being incorporated into a post-apartheid
defense force -- is always difficult and takes time, said the
defense minister.
</P>
<P>
The former freedom fighters from the armed wings of the ANC and
the PAC will have to gain experience before being given positions
of command in the 90,000 professional military, he said. 
</P>
