<HEADLINE> China On U.N. Peacekeeping Operations In Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 15 (Xinhua) --The general principles,
the purposes and principles of the United Nations Charter,
Neutrality and self-defense as well as the prior consent of the
parties, are the main principles to be followed in order to carry
out the U.N. peacekeeping operations in a more timely and
efficiently manner, China said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the open debate on the situation of Africa by the
United Nations Security Council, Chinese Ambassador to the U.N.,
Qin Huasun, said regarding to the peacekeeping operations in
Africa, the views of the countries concerned, the relevant
regional organizations and the U.N. Secretariat should be sought
widely beforehand when taking a decision.
</P>
<P>
The lack of guarantee for the security on the ground cannot be
taken as an excuse for taking a negative approach, and the lack of
sufficient resources have gravely impeded the normal functioning
of the peacekeeping operations, Qin said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the countries that are in arrears with the assess
peacekeeping operations to pay up their arrears in a prompt, full,
unconditional matter.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the peacekeeping operations in Sierra Leone, the
reaction of the security Council is not prompt and on the question
of the Democratic Republic of Congo, the Security Council was
very hesitant, which give a rise to a lot of suspicion of double
standards, the Ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
The key here lies in whether there is the necessary political
will or not, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
