The World Bank estimates that between 260 million and 300
million dollars are needed over the next three years for East
Timor's reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
East Timor, a former Portuguese colony, chose independence in
an August referendum. The United Nations sees a two-three-year
transition period needed for it to become fully independent.
</P>
<P>
During the period, a U.N. transitional administration is
mandated to take charge of all affairs in East Timor which
urgently needs humanitarian aid and infrastructure building.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
