<HEADLINE> Sudanese President to Restructure Ruling NCP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KHARTOUM, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President Omar al-
Bashir Wednesday vowed to restructure the ruling National Congress
Party (NCP) with a view to striking balance among the executive,
legislative and political organs of the country.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with representatives of Sudan's trade unions
 and businessmen, al-Bashir reviewed the reasons for which he made
his decision to dissolve the parliament headed by powerful Hassan
al-Turabi, who is also secretary-general of the NCP.
</P>
