 all parties concerned would continue to establish peace and
stability in the war-torn African state.
</P>
<P>
The recent decisions were designed to put an end to the
contraditions among the state institutions and the duality of
decision, he said, adding that they are aimed at unifying the
political leadership and enhancing the state prestige.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abdul-Rahim Ali, chief of good-offices committee
mediating between the government and legislative, said the two
sides were willing to reconcile. He pointed out that there were
several initiatives to heal the rift.
</P>
<P>
The committee made remarkable progress towards reconciliation,
the Sudanese News Agency quoted Ali as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The common grounds between the two sides in the country are
larger than the disputed points," he noted, adding that the
differences were transitory and confined to the leadership.
</P>
<P>
