Pakistani troops deployed at the LOC," a spokesman of the External
Affairs Ministry told the media here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman recalled that Pakistani Chief Executive Pervaiz
Musharraf had on October 17 announced withdrawal of troops only
from the international border between the two countries and
Pakistani officials had thereafter clarified that there was to be
no withdrawal of troops from the LOC.
</P>
<P>
Recent remarks attributed to the Pakistan Army spokesman were
only an "exercise in obfuscation," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the proposed reduction in defense expenditure as part of an
economic reforms package in Pakistan, the spokesman said New Delhi
had always desired economic stability and prosperity of the region
as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
