<HEADLINE> Meca Batters Gibraltar Straits Swim Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, Decmeber, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Spanish long-distance
swimmer David Meca became the fastest man to swim across the
Staits of Gibraltar from Tarifa of Spain on Thursday as he
continued his campaign against a doping ban.
</P>
<P>
Meca, the world long-distance swimming champion, spent two
hours 27 minutes in turbulent stretch of water to smash the listed
record of three hours 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard is under a four year doping ban slapped on him for
testing positive for the banned substance nandrolone at a world
cup meeting in Brazil in January.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee is to hear his appeal at
its Lausanne headquarters next week.
</P>
<P>
Meca's other exploits aimed at attracting attention to his case
include swimming with his feet chained from the notorious Alcatraz
prison to the San Francisco coastline, a distance of 2.5 km.
</P>
