<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Why Macao People Long for Return? (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- "The Chinese and Chinese hearts
are longing for return to the motherland." So reads an eye-
catching streamer on a 20-storey apartment building near the venue
for the upcoming Macao handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The streamer on the Jardim Hang Kei building is in fact one of
the huge streamers hung on Macao's high buildings or over the
streets, expressing Macao People's hope for "returning home".
Macao is to return to China on December 20 this year.
</P>
<P>
An old couple was choosing a TV set in a household electrical
appliances center on Almeida Avenue of downtown area. "Are you
going to take a daughter-in-law or marry away your daughter?" a
saleswoman asked the old couple.
</P>
<P>
"We don't want to miss any news programs about Macao's return (
to China)," the wife answered, explaining that they have an old TV
set they bought long time ago, and in case it does not work well
during the returning period, they have the new one.
</P>
<P>
U Yi Lam, 93, insisted that she go to the street to greet the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) troops to be stationed in
Macao despite she has to stand for a long time.
</P>
<P>
"Macao is returning home, and I have longed for the day all my
life," the nonagenarian said, adding that "the PLA troops are our
beloved people, and it's lucky for me to see them coming to Macao.
"
</P>
<P>
Macao people's patriotism has remained lofty despite centuries-
old separation from the motherland, for the peninsula has always
close contacts with the mainland in political, economic and
cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
In the Macao Hou Kong Middle School, for example, a five-star
national flag was hoisted on October 1st, 1949, to celebrate the
founding of the People's Republic of China. Ever since then, the
school has kept hoisting the Chinese national flag.
</P>
<P>
Governors of Macao were appointed by Portugal in the days of
Portuguese rule. Today, however, the Macao people have elected the
first Chief Executive of the Macao Special Administrative Region (
SAR).
</P>
<P>
"Macao's return inspires every public servant, and the
inspiration derives from a pride of being our own masters," said
Florida da Rosa Silva Chan, Secretary for Administration and
Justice of the Macao SAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
