<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee of CPPCC Marks 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 members of the Tibet
Autonomous Regional Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) gathered here today to celebrate
the 40th anniversary of the regional commitee.
</P>
<P>
The members, from all walks of life in the region, recalled the
great changes that have taken place in Tibet since the democratic
reforms in 1959.
</P>
<P>
Ranba Yongjim, a member of the Tibet Autonomous Regional
Committee of the CPPCC and vice president of Tibetan Women's
Federation, said that economic reforms 40 years ago brought the
Tibetan people into the socialist system from serfdom, and they
have been owners of the country ever since.
</P>
<P>
She said women cadres now make up over 30 percent of the region
's total leadership, and are involved in both political and
economic management in the region.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 health and medical care centers for women and
children have been set up in over 30 counties in Tibet, and the
infant mortality had dropped to about 3.6 percent last year from
43 percent 40 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Qiang Xiaolin, an agricultural expert, said Tibet's agriculture
and animal husbandry have grown fast in the past 20 years, and are
providing enough food and clothing for 94 percent of the Tibetan
people.
</P>
<P>
Other members also spoke highly of the great achievements made
in China under the leadership of the Communist Party, and pledged
to continue working for national unity, the prosperity of Tibet,
and reunification of the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Why Macao People Long for Return? (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Another factor behind their hope is that they have seen with
their own eyes the successful implementation of the policies of "
one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong"
and high-degree autonomy as well as the complete execution of the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the Macao people are fully confident of Macao's
return to China, said Prof. Ieong Wan Chong of University of Macao.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Macao people also hope for social stability
and economic recovery. As is known to all, the Chinese mainland
has long been providing Macao with capital, personnel, raw
materials, and daily necessities, making it possible for Macao to
have achieved today's success.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, the Macao people have also benefited from
the "effect of return". For example, police of both Macao and the
mainland have had good cooperation in cracking down cross-border
crimes and maintaining public order in Macao. And local residents
place high hopes on the PLA troops to be stationed in Macao in
this regard.
</P>
<P>
With the approaching of Macao's return, more and more mainland
tourists are coming to the region, and this will surely promote
the development of the local tourism industry, a key sector of the
Macao economy.  
</P>
