<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Claim Capturing 4 Villages in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tamil rebels said over their clandestine Voice of Tigers radio
that they have taken control of Uduthurai, Kodukkilai, Vembadi and
Mandalaai, all situated near Jaffna's southeastern coast, about
290 km north of capital Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The radio said five more guerrillas of Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) were killed in the confrontations with
government troops,bring the rebels' death toll to 65 during the
last five days of fighting.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels said Wednesday night that their offensive in
the Jaffna peninsula was continuing as LTTE commando units
tightened their grip around the military complex at Elephant Pass.
</P>
<P>
Elephant Pass is a strategically important causeway linking the
mainland with Jaffna peninsula. Government troops maintain a major
base there as a first line of defense protecting Jaffna,the former
stronghold of LTTE that the government retook in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Major General Lionel Balagalle told a new conference on
Wednesday that government troops have repulsed LTTE's repeated
attempts to overrun Elephant Pass, inflicting heavy casualties
among the rebels.
</P>
<P>
He said LTTE rebels could still try to launch fresh attempts on
the Elephant Pass base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
