<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs
in brief from the Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's peace deals with Syria and the
Palestinians will probably cause housing demand to exceed supply
over the next decade, said a study conducted recently by the Bureau
of Assessors.
</P>
<P>
The study said that after the peace deals reached with Syria and
the Palestinians, most of the Israeli settlers have to leave the
Golan Heights and some to leave the West Bank to settle down in
other places in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The most suitable places that the settlers will choose, the
study said, will be Tel Aviv, Haifa and the Beer Sheva area in the
south.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Aqua International, an American investment fund,
has signed a deal to purchase 25 percent of Eden Springs, the
Israeli mineral water company located at the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
The timing of the deal is significant in light of the resumption
of negotiations between Israel and Syria on the future of the Golan
Heights this week in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Aqua International will pay between 55 million U.S. dollars to
60 million for its stake.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel signed on Wednesday a new temporary
agreement with Canada to regulate flights arrangements between the
two countries, thereby ending a dispute over flights by the two
countries' national carriers for the time being.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal, Air Canada and El Al can now each operate seven
weekly flights between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Managing Director of the Iranian Fisheries
Organization Hamid Reza Shahmohammadi said here on Tuesday that the
sector has enjoyed a 100 percent growth during the second five-year
development plan (1995-2000).
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the plan, the canned fish food capacity was
about 120 million, but now it stood at 230 million while the number
of fish powder factories rose from 12 to 38 now, the Islamic
Republic News Agency quoted the official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The capacity of cold-storage units have increased from 23,000
tons to 78,000 tons in the said period, he said, and fish
production reached about 400,000 tons annually from 160,000 tons at
the beginning of the plan.
</P>
<P>
The official said that 27 fish processing factories and six
large fishing boats were also re-configured to meet the HCCP
European quality standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
