<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philadelphia 76ers won
their first game after top shooter Allen Iverson's comeback from
injury as they disposed off the Toronto Raptors 93-91 on Thursday
in Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
It was the second game for Iverson, who was held to 11 points
in a loss to Charlotte on his first game back, after he missed 10
games for a broken thumb and "The Answer" drilled in 37 points to
lead the Sixers on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
