pointers and contributed seven rebounds and seven assists.
</P>
<P>
Vince Carter, who led the Raptors with 19 points, missed a
winning chance in the dying seconds when his jumper from the left
corner bounced off the front of the rim.
</P>
<P>
Tracy McGrady added 18 points and Antonio Davis grabbed 18
rebounds for Toronto.
</P>
<P>
In San Antonio, David Robinson was the go-to guy as he scored
the last six points in a decisive 12-0 burst as the Spurs rallied
for an 83-77 victory over the Houston Rockets.
</P>
<P>
Tim Duncan led San Antonio with 20 points and 10 rebounds,
while Robinson finished with 14 points. Steve Francis scored 24
points to lead Houston.
</P>
<P>
In Wednesday's other games, the Charlotte Hornets edged out the
Minnesota Timberwolves 103-98 at home with Eddie Jones scored
seven of his 19 points in the final 48 seconds. Keith Van Horn
and Stephon Marbury combined for 50 points to lead the Nets for a
111-101 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, the Utah Jazz extended their winning streak to seven
games with a 96-86 victory over the Celtics, and in Orlando, the
Milwaukee Bucks routed the Magic 116-99.
</P>
<P>
The Indiana Pacers beat the hapless Chicago Bulls 102-91 on
home court and the Sacramento Kings held off the Grizzlies 109-106
in Vancouver. 
