<HEADLINE> 4 U.S. Airmen Injured in Copter Accident in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Four U.S. airmen based at
an air base in Kuwait have been released after receiving treatment
for minor injuries sustained from a helicopter accident, according
to a U.S. Embassy statement released here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The accident, which involved an HH-60 helicopter, occurred at
about 17:30 local time (14:30 GMT) Wednesday, 40 kilometers
southeast of the al-Jaber Air Base, located 80 kilometers south of
the capital.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is under investigation, said the
embassy statement, without giving more details.
</P>
<P>
This is the second air accident happened here to a U.S. plane
since last Friday, when three U.S. servicemen were killed and 17
others wounded in the crash landing of a U.S. C-130 military
transport aircraft at Kuwait International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The giant plane, carrying 96 U.S. military personnel, made an
emergency landing after it sustained a defect in the main landing
gear. 
</P>
