<HEADLINE> World Cup Leader Kostelic Injured in Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Cup overall leader
Janica Kostelic was injured heavily after a big crash in a
downhill training session on Thursday in St Moritz, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian teenager, 17, fell on her back after coming off a
jump and careered into safety netting.
</P>
<P>
Swiss radio reported she had torn ligaments in her right knee
and could be sidelined for up to six months. 
</P>
