<HEADLINE> Singapore Foreign Minister to Attend Macao Handover Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Foreign Minister
Shunmugam Jayakumar will represent his country at the Macao
handover ceremony, the Foreign Ministry (MFA) announced in a press
statement Thursday.
</P>
<P>
MFA said that Jayakumar will make an official visit to Macao
from December 17-21,1999, where he will meet Edmund Ho Hau Wah,
chief executive-designate of the Macao Special Administrative
Region of China.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore delegation will also include Singapore's counsel-
general in Hong Kong, MFA added.
</P>
<P>
Macao, a peninsula very close to the financial hub Hong Kong,
is to return to China on December 20 after being ruled by the
Portuguese for more than 150 years. 
</P>
