<HEADLINE> Chinese Workers Urged to Engage in SOE Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the second plenary session of the 13th Executive
Council of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU),Hu
said that workers should play a bigger role in and make greater
contribution to structural adjustment, transformation of
enterprises' mechanism, management improvement, and market
expansion.
</P>
<P>
He also asked trade unions to work harder to protect and
develop the rights and interests of its workers.
</P>
<P>
Trade unions should actively support Party committees and
governments at all levels in their bid to resolve workers'
complaints and deal harshly with cases in which their rights and
interests are violated, he said.
</P>
<P>
Relying whole-heartedly on the working class is necessary to
strengthen Party leadership and the socialist system as well as an
important prerequisite for good and sound management of China's
industry, Hu stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that trade unions should be provide support and
guidance for workers and make greater efforts to strengthen trade
unions at the grassroots.
</P>
<P>
Hu called on the trade unions to carry out sound ideological
work, emphasizing the need to further educate its workers on
patriotism, collectivism and socialism.
</P>
<P>
He also urged trade unions to help those workers in financial
difficulty, especially as the New Year is approaching, so that
they can feel the warmth of socialism. 
</P>
