<HEADLINE> Alaskan Skiers Wagner and Flora Win in Continental Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Alaska skiers Wendy Wagner and
Lars Flora won women's and men's sprints respectively Wednesday
night in the Continental Cup cross-country ski series in Canmore,
Canada.
</P>
<P>
On the opening night of the event, Wagner won the women's race
on the 1.5-kilometer Nordic track. Canadian skier Jaime Fortier
took the second place, while countrywomen Milaine Theriault and
Tara Whitten ranked third and fourth.
</P>
<P>
In the men's counterpart, Flora beat George Grey of Canada and
Andrew Johnson of the United States to take the title. Junior
skier Canadian Mike Argue took fourth place.
</P>
<P>
Sprints have become an official medal event on the World Cup
and Continental Cup circuits since they were introduced as a
demonstration event three years ago. The races range from 400
meters to 1.5 kilometers in distance.
</P>
<P>
The Continental Cup series continues Saturday. 
</P>
