<HEADLINE> Hong Kong CE to Attend Macao Handover Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong SAR of China, will lead a Hong Kong
delegation to Macao on Sunday to attend Macao Handover Ceremony, a
Government spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Tung would attend the ceremony and other
related events as a member of the Chinese government delegation.
</P>
<P>
Among the delegation are the Chief Justice, the Chief Secretary
for Administration, the Financial Secretary and the Secretary for
Justice. The delegation comprises 45 members.
</P>
<P>
During Tung's absence, the Financial Secretary and the
Secretary for Justice, who will visit Macao at different times on
the two days, will take turn to act as Chief Executive. 
</P>
