<HEADLINE> Strike Forces Air France to Cancel Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A strike by plane oil supply
workers and weather-service workers forced France's national
carrier Air France to cancel more than 40 percent of its flights
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We are always suffering from strikes by oil supply workers, to
which has been added a strike by aeronautic weather-service
workers, which is making conditions for operations even more
difficult," said Air France.
</P>
<P>
The national union of weather service workers announced a two-
day strike Wednesday to protest the air company's budget, while
oil supply workers are staging a one-day strike in the airports of
Paris and other major cities. 
</P>
