<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NDCC report did not mention of any casualties but radio
reports said one was killed in Cebu, another was electrocuted.
</P>
<P>
According to the NDCC, the Visayas tremble was strongest in
Leyte province with a magnitude of 6.0 on the Richter Scale.
Several buildings, schools and offices in the Visayas sustained
minor damage in the earthquake, which came from the Philippine
fault zone.
</P>
<P>
NDCC Chairman Orlando Mercado has directed local officials to
conduct an assessment of damage in their respective areas of
jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, a powerful earthquake with a magnitude of 6.8 on
the Richter Scale hit Luzon, killing 6 and wounding 37 others.
