<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Young Environmental Protectors Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Children from 100 Beijing
schools who are members of the Hand in Hand Global Village (HHGV)
were awarded here today at a conference.
</P>
<P>
Aiming to promote environmental protection awareness for
children, the China Children's Hand in Hand Global Village was set
up on April 22, the International Earth Day, in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The activity was initiated by the Chinese Children's News in
1990 and the Beijing 100-school HHGV announced its opening on
January 17 this year. In the past year, the 100 schools have held
a number of events to clean up the environment such as the rubbish
picking up at Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
As of November, four Hand in Hand Environmental Protection
schools had been set up in the poverty stricken areas of Jiangxi,
Gansu and Shanxi provinces, with funds collected through children'
s trash recycling projects. Two in northwest China's Gansu
Province were build with money from Beijing schools.
</P>
<P>
The money was also used to buy trees for planting in the
Yellow River and Yangtse River basins to prevent soil erosion.
</P>
</TEXT>
