<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Police Well Prepared for New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 16 (Xinhua) - The Hong Kong SAR Police
Force is fully prepared to mobilise sufficient manpower for
policing duties during celebrations to mark the new millennium,
Assistant Commissioner of Police, Cheung Chi-shum, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Ninety-five per cent of the strength of the operational
formations is being maintained, and this arrangement is expected
to last until mid January 2000," he said at a press conference on
Police preparations for the millennium celebration activities,
</P>
<P>
"Police presence will be maximised on the streets so that the
public may seek assistance from patrolling police officers direct
in case of emergency," Cheung added.
</P>
<P>
As most of the celebration activities would be held on the Y2K
critical moments, Cheung said Police would maintain close liaison
with other government departments and policy bureaus to ensure
that the community as a whole would not be affected by any Y2K-
induced or other unforeseen incidents.
</P>
<P>
"About 14,000 Police officers, including Auxiliary Police
personnel, will be deployed to maintain order and direct traffic
on New Year's Eve," he said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that all the computer systems of the Force were Y2K
compliant, Cheung said Police were confident that Police operation
would not be affected.
</P>
<P>
"On Y2K sensitive dates, task forces and enhanced manning of
Police control centres will be effected round the clock.
</P>
<P>
As part of the millennium celebration period will coincide with
the Christmas and New Year holidays as well as the run-up to the
Lunar New Year, Police will also take preventive measures against
crimes common in the festive season.
</P>
<P>
"Everything will be under control to ensure a smooth transition
to the new millennium," Cheung said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
