<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Export 250,000 Tons of Rice to HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has signed a deal
with Hong Kong to provide the territory with 250,000 tons of rice
next year, the Commerce Ministry confirmed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Grain Division under the Ministry's Foreign Trade
Department told Xinhua that the deal was between Thailand's
Association of Rice Exporters and Hong Kong's Association of Rice
Exporters and Importers.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, Bangkok would export 250,000 tons of rice to
Hong Kong in 2000, the same amount as this year, with a
possibility of 10 percent variation.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Ministry said that Thai rice had so far maintained
its largest market share in Hong Kong, particularly the renowned
jasmine rice due to its unique taste.
</P>
<P>
From January to October, Thailand exported 206,262 tons of rice
to Hong Kong, with Thai jasmine rice accounting for the largest
proportion with 268,673 tons, the Commerce Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's total rice exports in the first ten months of this
year reached 5.26 million tons, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
