<HEADLINE> "Israel in Chinese Eyes" Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 Xinhua)-- An exhibition themed "Israel in
Chinese Eyes", co-sponsored by the Chinese Folk Literature and Art
Society and the Israeli Embassy in China, opened at the Museum of
Chinese History here today.
</P>
<P>
On display are outstanding works by Chinese folk artists who
have visited Israel. The works, including wood carvings, paintings,
photos and sculptures, reflect the lifestyle and traditional
culture of Israel, and demonstrate the friendship between the
Chinese and Israeli peoples.
</P>
<P>
Israeli ambassador to China Ora Namir and Zhou Jue, president
of the China-Israel Friendship Association, were among those
present at the opening ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
