<HEADLINE> France Warns Israel, Syria Not to Sacrifice Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine said Thursday that Israel and Syria are having a good
chance to make peace, but they should not sacrifice the
Palestinians in their deal.
</P>
<P>
"The peace in the Middle East should be total," he said in an
interview with Radio-Television Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
He said Israel and Syria, after making profound calculations,
have decided to engage in a peace process rather than keeping the
status quo.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said that it is now easier for Israel to
make peace with Syria than with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"Our vigilance will be to make sure that the Palestinians not
be sacrificed in this affair,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Syria resumed their peace talks on Wednesday in
Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
