<HEADLINE> 11 People Killed in Taxi Crash in S.Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed
and four seriously injured in a four-vehicle pile-up outside
Komatipoort in Mpumalanga of South Africa on Thursday, South
African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The taxi was on its way to Maputo in Mozambique when it crashed
into the back of a truck on a hill about 20 km outside Komatipoort
at about 4.30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
Komatipoort chief traffic officer Bokkie Burger said the taxi
overturned and the passengers were flung onto the road. A second
truck slammed into the first truck, then was hit by another
minibus taxi.
</P>
<P>
Burger said the second taxi tried to swerve and drove over some
of the people lying on the road.
</P>
<P>
Mpumalanga police spokesman Captain Ben Mkhonto said all those
killed were from the first minibus taxi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
