<HEADLINE> JMC Leaves for Congo Over War Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A special committee of the
Joint Military Commission (JMC) on the Democratic Republic of the
Congo (DRC) left here Thursday morning for the DRC, targeting the
release of war prisoners in the African country.
</P>
<P>
The committee would work out plans on how to have access to
Ekele, a town in which some 700 Zimbabwean and Namibian troops are
currently surrounded by the rebel Rally for Congolese Democracy
soldiers, an official working in the JMC office based in Lusaka
told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Humanitarian corridors, release of war prisoners,
disengagement of troops and disarmament of all armed groups in the
DRC were among the main issues adopted at the just ended third JMC
plenary session in Zimbabwe. 
</P>
