<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computer Virus Plays Havoc in Addis Ababa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Computer systems in
several government offices, business concerns and non-governmental
organizations in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia became paralyzed under the
attack of a computer virus early this week, informed sources said
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to local experts, the unidentified computer virus was
 programmed to trigger havoc on December 13, it must have been
transmitted from one terminal to another through diskettes or
perhaps the e-mail system over a long period of time.
</P>
<P>
Most of the anti-virus available in Addis Ababa does not
recognize this virus, which destructs all system files and folders
in the affected computers, local computer dealers said.
</P>
<P>
An unconfirmed report said a local bank and computer dealer
were also among those victimized.
</P>
<P>
The experts have warned computer users to install virus
scanners and exercise utmost caution in using diskettes from
outside their offices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
