<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Creditor Banks Reach Outline Agreement on GDE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The working group of banks
to Guangdong Enterprise (GDE) announced Thursday that it has
reached an agreement-in-principle with the Guangdong government
and its advisers for the restructuring of GDE.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is subject to the agreement of the financial
creditor group as a whole and details will be given to them at an
all-bank meeting early next year.
</P>
<P>
"Both sides have been patient and constructive throughout
discussion," said Wang Qishan, executive vice-governor of the
People's Government of Guangdong Province. "This agreement
demonstrates the Guangdong government's commitment to the
international financial markets," he added.
</P>
<P>
Mervyn Davies, of Standard Chartered, the liaison bank in the
Steering Committee, said that it is a positive step forward in
resolving a long, complex and very difficult problem.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides that in exchange for their existing debt,
banks will be offered a package of instruments including notes
from Dongshen Water Supply Company injected in Guangdong
Investment, various debt instruments of GDE companies, real estate
and equity participation in certain related companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
