<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in
Tokyo Thursday, with the key Nikkei index falling for the fourth
straight trading day.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 27.05 points, or 0.15
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 18,111.31.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, the broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX),
which covers all First Section issues, rose 5.27 points or 0.33
percent to 1,618.22.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section went up to 574.42 million shares
from Wednesday's 540.39 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Heavy Industries was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Trading remained inactive, with many foreign investors heading
off for Christmas holidays, traders said.
</P>
<P>
While the establishment of new investment trusts underpinned
overall share prices, a wait-and-see attitude has prevailed in the
market due to fears about the Y2K computer bug, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers far
outnumbered gainers 833 to 406, with 112 issues remaining
unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
