<HEADLINE> Liaoning Reports Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The combined industrial
output of Liaoning Province, an industrial giant in northeast
China, reached 28.3 billion yuan in November, up 10.6 percent from
the same 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
The increase rate was 6.2 and 6.9 percentage points higher than
those of October and September, respectively, on a yearly basis,
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The province's state-owned industries and private businesses
with annual sales income exceeding five million yuan report an
aggregate industrial output of 250.3 billion yuan in the first
eleven months of this year, representing a year-on-year increase
of 9.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Both sales and industrial production increased in the 11-month
period of this year. At the same time, the province's exports rose
8.2 percent in the first ten months of this year. 
</P>
