<HEADLINE> Villagers in Poorest Region Move into New Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 2,730 rural
households in Guyuan Prefecture of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region in northwest China have moved into new homes thanks to a
settlement project.
</P>
<P>
The regional government launched the project earlier this year
to help hundreds of villagers living in run-down houses by
allocating and raising money to build or renovate unsafe houses.
</P>
<P>
They collected 5.64 million yuan (670,000 US dollars) and built
or renovated 6,974 houses with the money. The houses cover an area
of 116,300 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The settlement project is part of the poverty relief efforts
undertaken by the regional government to lift the prefecture out
of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Guyuan Prefecture is one of the poorest area in China, and for
more than a decade the central and regional governments have made
tremendous efforts to help the poor people living there secure a
better life. 
</P>
