<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Manufacturing Sector Grows 27 Percent in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's manufacturing
sector grew by 27.5 percent in October this year over that in the
same month last year, according to the Statistics Department
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This was a double-digit growth in the sector for the seventh
consecutive month since April on a year-on-year basis, it said in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
However, there was a marginal drop of 0.4 percent in the sales
value of the current month amounting to 23.2 billion ringgit (6.
105 billion U.S. dollars) in comparison with 23.3 billion ringgit
(6.131 billion U.S. dollars) in September, the department said.
</P>
<P>
During the first 10 months of the year, the total sales value
in the manufacturing sector stood at 208.3 billion ringgit (54.815
billion U.S. dollars), representing an increase of 13.5 percent
from 183.6 billion ringgit (48.315 billion U.S. dollars) in the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of employees engaged in the manufacturing sector at
the end of October grew by 8.3 percent to a total of 962,593
persons against 888,827 persons at the end of the same month in
1998, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
