<HEADLINE> Indonesian Govt Asked to Try Human Right Abusers in Aceh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's House of
Representative (DPR) Thursday issued a recommendation to the
government on the settlement of Aceh issue.
</P>
<P>
In its recommendation, the House pressed the government soon to
bring into justice those who have allegedly involved in the human
right abuse and committed atrocities in the predominantly Muslim
province of Aceh.
</P>
<P>
"It is important that human right abusers and those who had
committed atrocities in the province be brought to justice very
soon," said Ali Yahya, spokesman of the House special committee on
Aceh case.
</P>
<P>
The recommendation was endorsed by the plenary session here
Thursday after the House's special team on Aceh completed its task
in collecting data and information in connection with the Aceh
case.
</P>
<P>
Aceh, the most-western province of Indonesia, now has been
demanding a referendum for independence from the unitary state of
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The demands for referendum and self determination was sponsored
by the Free Aceh Movement (GAM), an underground movement in the
province which had been launching a fighting against central
government over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid earlier had agreed to conduct a
referendum in Aceh, but it was not intended to give a chance for
the province to separate from Indonesia, saying the government
would not tolerate any kind of separatist movements.
</P>
<P>
"The Aceh affair is not merely a local issue, but has been a
national issue which should be solved very soon. Human right
abusers have to be tried as soon as possible," Yahya said.
</P>
<P>
But however the recommendation didn't specify the referendum
demands which now have been asked by Acehnese.
</P>
<P>
"And referendum demands from Acehnese have to be discussed
seriously and comprehensively," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
