<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao on Track of Economic Recovery (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Macao's industrial output value totaled 15.57 billion patacas
in 1998 and 70 percent of its industrial products were sold on
overseas markets. Macao is now restructuring its industry in an
attempt to change its economy's excessive reliance on a single
source for revenue generation -- tourism and gambling -- and lack
of complementarity among its major economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Economic Services of the Macao government
said that China's accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO)
is not expected to affect Macao's export industry adversely. On
the contrary, observers from both Macao and the Chinese mainland
say that the openness of the mainland market will draw more funds
and technology into Macao.
</P>
<P>
After it reverts to Chinese rule, Macao will become an
effective window for exchanges -- economic, trade, and otherwise --
between the mainland and the rest of the world. Macao has
established trade links with more than 120 countries and regions
in the world and participated in a number of international
economic organizations. After December 20, 1999, Macao will
continue to be a member of many international organizations and a
signatory of many international treaties. For example, Macao will
continue to enjoy trade arrangements as a member of the WTO.
</P>
<P>
So far Macao's international airport links the region with
about 30 cities around the world. By 2000, it is expected to
receive 2.5 million passengers a year to become one of the air
transportation hubs in south China.
</P>
<P>
As Macao's handover approaches, the Macao pataca, which is
freely convertible, has remained stable. Since the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) to be established on December 20 will
maintain a high degree of autonomy in tax, finance, currency and
tariff policies, Macao will become even more internationalized
after its return to China. It is expected to maintain its status
as a successful mini-economy in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
