<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Strengthen Economic Cooperation with Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China will strengthen economic cooperation with Macao, a
senior official from the municipal foreign trade and economic
committee told Xinhua recently.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing will introduce advanced management method in finance
and tourism sectors from Macao after China enters the World Trade
Organization (WTO), said Wang Jiguang, deputy director of the
committee.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has established trade ties with Macao in the 1980s.
As the country's largest textile production base in southwest
China, Chongqing supplied large sums of textile raw materials to
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the 1990s, economic and trade relations
between the two sides have developed rapidly.
</P>
<P>
By the end of September, Chongqing had approved 29 Macao-funded
enterprises, with contractual investment totaling 41.67 million U.
S. dollars. These projects cover real estate, recreation and
hardware sectors.
</P>
<P>
Last April, China, Portugal and Macao signed an agreement for
the construction of a bridge on the Jialingjiang river. The work,
which will involve an investment of 80 million U.S. dollars,
started today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
