<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Govt to Give General Amnesty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government
would soon give a general abolition and amnesty to all political
detainees nationwide, a senior official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We will do so in a couple of weeks. Before the end of the year,
we expect it (the awarding of abolition and amnesty) will be
completed," Minister of Law and Legislation Yusril Ihza Mahendra
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
He said that his side now had been collecting a comprehensive
data and making list of all political prisoners across the country.
</P>
<P>
"We have been collecting and listing those that will be given
abolition and amnesty," he added.
</P>
<P>
"This is a sensitive matter as it can trigger jealousy from
other prisoners (out of political detainees). We have to pay our
attention on this. You know other prisoners will demand (abolition
and amnesty) too," he said.
</P>
<P>
On December 10, the government had released 91 political
detainees nationwide including East Timorese and the People
Democratic Party (PRD) activists who were sent into prison by the
former president Soeharto regime.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid had also agreed on Wednesday to
endorse the House of Representative's recommendation on the
release of all political prisoners nationwide in a bid to respect
human right and uphold democratic value in Indonesia. 
</P>
