<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on Cross-Straits Economy and Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The increasing economic
cooperation between the mainland and Taiwan in recent years will
benefit the future growth of both sides.
</P>
<P>
According to experts attending an ongoing seminar on future
cross-straits economic development held in this capital of east
China's Zhejiang Province, the continuous investment from Taiwan
in the mainland ranks second after Hong Kong, and leads the United
States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The accumulative total cross-straits trade value stood at 136.9
billion US dollars by the end of last year. In 1998, the trade
value between the two sides reached 20.5 billion US dollars, 3.87
billion in imports from the mainland to Taiwan and 16.6 billion
from Taiwan to the mainland, said the experts.
</P>
<P>
Over the past ten years, Taiwan business people have set up 41,
000 joint-ventures in the mainland with a total investment of 42
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The economists from a dozen of research institutes and
universities in Taiwan and the mainland noted that the potential
market and favorable policies in the mainland are attractive to
Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
They urged for the direct exchange of postal services, trade,
and air and shipping services across the Taiwan Straits. The
exchange will help both sides maintain economic vitality and
develop future prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Improves Water Supply Facilities to Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Zhuhai, the nearest interior
city to Macao, has been working to improve facilities capable of
supplying water to Macao year-round.
</P>
<P>
According to Tang Lihua, manager of the Zhuhai Water Supply
Company, which is in charge to providing drinking water to Macao,
the company now operates three networks that help send 150,000
cubic meters of fresh water from Zhuhai to Macao daily.
</P>
<P>
But owing to the natural conditions in the locality, every
October through March the fresh-water supply from Zhuhai to Macao
is adversely affected when seawater flows into the fresh-water
source.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the dilemma during that period, Tang's company has
built a water diversion system that will relocate the present
water-drawing position 40 km away to avoid the negative impact of
the refluent seawater.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, construction of another new pumping station is
underway at a cost of 280 million yuan (33.7 million US dollars).
When the station is finished, 1.3 million cu m of fresh water will
be pumped daily.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, a third water supply project will also be
built by installing a water pipeline connecting Zhuxiandong
Reservoir of Zhuhai to Qingzhou Water Plant of Macao. The project
is expected to be completed in two years, according to Tang.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
