<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Home of Terra-Cotta Warriors to Attract More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Lingtong District of Xi'an
City, the capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, has
planned to achieve 2.2 billion yuan (265 million US dollars) in
tourism income in 2010, or 32 percent of its GDP in the year.
</P>
<P>
Lingtong, home of the Terra-Cotta Warriors, one of the world's
eight wonders, is 30 km east of Xi'an, and has received 6.18
million domestic and foreign tourists so far this year. The income
from tourism accounted for one-fourth of the district's total
financial revenue this year.
</P>
<P>
There are a host of scenic spots in the district, such as the
Qinshihuang Mausoleum, which has been put on the World Heritage
list, the museum displaying the Terra-Cotta Warriors, and the
Huaqingchi, an imperial park of the Tang Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an, which has served as the capital of 13 imperial dynasties,
is a popular tourist destination because of its numerous sites of
historical interest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0278 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Pottery Workshop Unearthed in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists
recently confirmed that a pottery workshop previously excavated in
Jiaozuo in Henan Province, central China, was built during the
early Warring States Period (475-221 B.C.).
</P>
<P>
Along with the workshop, some ten tombs of the Han Dynasty (206
B.C.- A.D. 220) were also discovered at a construction site near
the building.
</P>
<P>
Many gray-colored clay containers of various shapes and designs
were unearthed in the workshop, and among them archeologists found
a square-shaped seal with the words "pottery workshop" in Chinese
on the handle of one container.
</P>
<P>
Local experts say this find provides more significant
information for determining the age of local cultural relics.
Further research and protection of the workshop and tombs is now
underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
