<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Low-Cost Housing Popular in Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Economy housing has become
increasingly popular in the port city of Dalian in northeast China
's Liaoning Province since the government did away with the
decades-old welfare housing distribution system last year.
</P>
<P>
Although the price per square meter of space in some
residential communities has increased to 3,200 yuan (385 US
dollars ) this year from 2,500 to 2,800 yuan (300-337 US dollars)
last year, the supply of affordable housing still does not meet
demand, according to one estate agent.
</P>
<P>
In other residential communities, the average price per square
meter is 2,500 yuan (300 US dollars), attracting hundreds of
buyers.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the booming business in affordable housing
to their relatively lower prices, good quality of construction,
and efficient design.
</P>
<P>
The great improvement in living conditions for the local
residents of Dalian contributes significantly to the hot market,
analysts say.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, they noted, real estate markets nationwide still
remain sluggish because of inadequate demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
