<HEADLINE> Seminar Probes Development of Sino-African Relationship in 21st Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua)-- One hundred and fifty
government officials, African studies scholars, and business
representatives stressed the significance of promoting Sino-
African relations at a seminar which concluded here today.
</P>
<P>
The Seminar on 21st Century Development Strategy for Sino-
African Relations, held from December 14 to 16, was hosted by the
Chinese Research Society of African Affairs (CRSAA).
</P>
<P>
During the three day seminar, representatives learned about the
guidelines set by President Jiang Zemin for the development of
Sino-African relations, and heard reports from officials from the
Foreign Ministry, Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, the International Department of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, and the Overseas Chinese Affairs
Office of the State Council, on the political relations and
economic cooperation and exchanges between the political parties
and peoples of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The representatives also took part in comprehensive, in-depth,
and thorough discussions on the progress of Sino-African studies
over the past 50 years, as well as on the prospects for their
development in the next century.
</P>
<P>
They vowed to strengthen efforts for building a stable, long-
term, friendly Sino-African relationship oriented toward the 21st
century, which will involve comprehensive and more vigorous
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The CRSAA, the only Chinese academic organization devoted to
African issues, has 540 members, and since its founding 20 years
ago has achieved enormous academic progress and trained many
researchers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
