<P>
SEOUL, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A ferry route linking Sokcho
city on the eastern coast of South Korea and Hunchun city of China
via the Russian Far East is expected to open in March.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Maritime Affairs and Fisheries said Thursday
that it has granted a license to a South Korean-Chinese joint
venture to operate the ferry service on the condition that it
launches a car ferry service and sets up a passenger terminal in
Sokcho.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed to provide a car ferry service on the
Sokcho-Hunchun route in 1993. The joint venture was allowed to go
ahead with the project by the government of the Russian Far East
in June.
</P>
<P>
The new route is expected to stimulate economic exchanges
between South Korea, the three northeastern provinces of China and
the Russian Far East, said a ministry spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
