<HEADLINE> Macao's Return Great Contribution to Peace: Maltese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Maltese President Guido De Marco
Wednesday congratulated China on Macao's return and praised the
event as a great contribution to world peace, reports from
Valletta said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a picture show on Macao sponsored by the Chinese
embassy in Malta, De Marco applauded Macao's return as a great
contribution to world peace, noting Chinese and Portuguese efforts
in peacefully settling the hundreds-year issue through dialogues.
</P>
<P>
The "one country, two systems" policy, initiated by the late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and proved out by Hong Kong's
successful return, has become an effective solution to pending
problems left by history, said the president.
</P>
<P>
De Marco said the policy has now created a dialogue bridge for
China and Portugal to smoothly settle the Macao issue, by
guaranteeing both Macao's return to China and the continuance of
its current social system.
</P>
<P>
He also hailed Macao's return as a successful example of
China's peaceful diplomacy, which fully reflects the country's
arts of far-sighted diplomacy and pragmatic diplomatic policy.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Malta Zu Qinshun, who jointly presided
over the opening ceremony with De Marco, briefed the guests of the
facts about Macao's return and principles of "one country, two
systems," "Macao people governing Macao" and "a high degree of
autonomy." 
</P>
