<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Containers Handled At Shanghai Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A record four million TEUs of
containers have been reported to be handled at Shanghai Port since
early this year, one million TEUs more than in the whole of 1998,
the largest year-on-year increase that has reported so far.
</P>
<P>
Huang Ju, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and secretary of the CPC
Shanghai Municipal Committee, has sent a congratulatory message
for the fast growth of its container shipping.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai port, which launched its first international container
shipping route back in 1978, has now ranked itself among the world
's top ten ports in terms of the amount of container shipping.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai port handled 1.19 million TEUs of containers in 1994,
and the figure jumped to 3.06 million in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In total, Shanghai port has inaugurated 16 international
container shipping routes, which link the China's largest
industrial center with more than 120 ports worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
