<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Regional Flag and Emblem of Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The regional flag and emblem of
the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) are symbols and
insignias of the Macao SAR. They came into being on March 31, 1993.
</P>
<P>
The regional flag of the Macao SAR is a green flag with five
stars, lotus flower, bridge and sea water.
</P>
<P>
The five stars symbolize national unification and the fact that
Macao is an inalienable part of China. Lotus flower is a popular
local flower in Macao. In the old days, Macao was also known as
the "land of lotus" and "lotus stem." Its three petals represent
the Macao Peninsula, Taipa Island and Coloane Island. The whole
lotus flower symbolizes the prosperity of the future of Macao. The
bridge and sea water below the lotus flower reflect the natural
conditions of Macao. And the green flag symbolizes the thriving
land of China including Macao.
</P>
<P>
The regional emblem of the Macao SAR is composed of five stars,
lotus flower, bridge and sea water encircled by the words "Macao
Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China"
in Chinese and "MACAO" in Portuguese. This shows that both Chinese
and Portuguese are official languages in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The regional flag and emblem of the Macao SAR are designed to
highlight the highly autonomous status of the Macao SAR and to
provide convenience for it in communications with the outside
world. According to Article 10 of the Basic Law, apart from
displaying the national flag and emblem of the People's Republic
of China, the Macao SAR may also display and use a regional flag
and a regional emblem.
</P>
<P>
The regional flag and emblem of the Macao SAR are results of
collective wisdom and creation. The Macao SAR Basic Law Drafting
Committee collected 782 design works of the regional flag and
emblem from all over the country, including Macao. Then three sets
of design were selected from all the works. Finally, the Macao SAR
Basic Law Drafting Committee put together the merits of all design
works and put forward a new design. The design of the regional
flag and emblem were approved by the first session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC) as it passed the Basic Law of the
Macao SAR on March 31, 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991216.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Researchers Make Breakthrough in Extracting Hydrogen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A research team in Anshan, a city in northeast China's Liaoning
province, claimed that they have invented equipment, which can
produce hydrogen with lower electricity use. They said the
equipment uses only 0.93 kilowatts/hour to make one cubic meter of
hydrogen gas -- believed to be the lowest figure in the world.
</P>
<P>
Before the equipment was invented, the researchers here were
using about 8 kilowatt/hour to turn out one cubic meter of
hydrogen.
</P>
<P>
However, local hydrogen producers noted that large-scale
production of hydrogen with this equipment will still be quite
costly. About 26 to 36 billion yuan (3.1 to 4.3 billion US dollars)
is needed to build a coastal plant with daily capacity of 100
million cubic gas based on this technology.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the research team was reported to have developed even
more sophisticated equipment which used only 0.0093 kilowatt/hour
to produce one cubic meter of hydrogen, but scientists said that
there are too many difficulties involved and the cost of making
such equipment and accessories is prohibitive.
</P>
<P>
Virtually pollution-free hydrogen is expected to replace other
conventional fuels in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
The research outcome is expected to be published on the
Internet shortly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
