<HEADLINE> World Bank Aids Sri Lanka's Agricultural Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has approved a
loan of 27 million U.S. dollars for an Irrigated Agricultural
project in Northeast Sri Lanka, the official Daily News reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The project is to support efforts to re-establish communities
affected by ethnic conflict in the Northeast region by reviving
agricultural production which is the basic community level service,
the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at the immediate rehabilitation needs and
capacity building of displayed agricultural communities.
</P>
<P>
It will benefit about 24,000 families living in 400 villages in
the Northeast region.
</P>
<P>
It will finance rehabilitation of irrigation schemes and rural
roads, provision of drinking water and community capacity building
activities, said the reports, adding that agricultural
productivity of about 16,000 hectares will be revitalized by
restoring 400 neglected irrigation schemes.
</P>
<P>
The service capacity of the 1,200 kilometers of priority
village roads will be rehabilitated, connecting rural villages to
irrigation schemes and markets and supporting the transfer of
goods, services and people, the reports added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
