<HEADLINE> Indonesian Management Board to Help Fund Olympics Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian State Secretary
AliRahman has approved the Gelora Senayan Management Board's (BPGS)
planto financially assist the National Sports Council (KONI) in
itspreparations for athletes competing in the Olympic Games next
year.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Gelora Senayan Executive Directors (DPGS)
YasidiHambali said that Ali, who is also BPGS chairman, had agreed
to handover 2 billion rupiah (276,000 U.S. dollars) to enable
KONI start itscentralized training program on February 1.
</P>
<P>
"Based on our meeting on Tuesday evening, the state secretary
agreed to help KONI. However, the DPGS's help was only
complimentary. The government must take full responsibility in
financing the trainingprograms," Yasidi was quoted by the Jakarta
Post Thursday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Yasidi said Ali would meet with BPGS's vice chairman, State
Minister of Youth Affairs and Sports Mahadi Sinambela, and KONI'
schairman Wismoyo Arismunandar to discuss the mechanism to
contributefunds for national sports development in the future.
</P>
<P>
"We don't want the decision to be made only by BPGS's chairman,
butrather collectively by the three parties," he said.
</P>
<P>
KONI has requested 6.9 billion rupiah from the government
tofinance its Olympic training program, but it has yet to receive
anyresponse. It has also asked BPGS to provide 5 billion rupiah
and BPGShas approved to hand over 2 billion rupiah in advance.
</P>
