<HEADLINE> E-Business Network Set up in East China Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- An electronic business network
linking telephone users in four major cities in east China's
Shandong with local financial organizations and commercial
businesses will become operational soon.
</P>
<P>
The network will provide a series of financial and banking
services such as account payment, trade dealing and information
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Shandong will institute favorable policies to encourage more
such networks with services for E-commerce, advertising,
entertainment, video programs and medical consultation.
</P>
<P>
By 2005, the province will have combined its current three
networks: telecommunication, cable television and computer systems.
</P>
<P>
The province has so far opened a number of websites providing
digital data, Internet service and information on public
multimedia and automatic wide-band multimedia.
</P>
<P>
The network was jointly set up by a local telecom firm and an
agriculture bank to improve Shandong's information and economic
development. 
</P>
