<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index
on the Buenos Aires Exchange stood at 536.70 points against
Wednesday's 536.71 points, nearly the same.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 31.494 million U.S. dollars against 29.388
million dollars on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank interest rate fell to 9.25 percent in the
24-hour term from 9.3 percent on the previous day. The exchange
rate of the Argentine peso against the dollar remained unchanged
at 0.998 for purchase and 1.003 for sale. 
</P>
