<HEADLINE> Ghedina Fastest in Men's Downhill Practice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Local hero Kristian Ghedina
clocked the fastest time in Wednesday's opening practice of a
World Cup men's downhill event on the Saslong piste in Val Gardena,
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Ghedina posted a time of two minutes 06.55 seconds as he
prepared for the two World Cup races on Friday and Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Hannes Trinkl was second in 2:07.21, with Canadian
Darin McBeath third with a time of 2:08.21.
</P>
<P>
Austria's World Cup leader Hermann Maier had to settle for the
12th, for which he blamed on the piste being too soft and slow
compared to previous years. 
