<HEADLINE> German Court Sentences Bosnian Serb to Life Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A court in Munich, Germany,
sentenced a Bosnian Serb to life jail on Wednesday on charges of "
genocide" during the Bosnian conflicts, the Deutsche Presse
Agentur (DPA) news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
German state prosecutors said that Djuradj Kusljic, 44, had
taken part in the expulsions and killings of Muslims during the
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The court met the demand of prosecutors for a life term after
hearing 60 witnesses.
</P>
<P>
But the defendant denied the charges and his lawyers called for
an acquittal.
</P>
<P>
Kusljic was reported to have arrived in Munich as a war refugee
in 1993. Five years later he was arrested in an apartment in the
city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
