<HEADLINE> Moldova Captain in Critical Condition after Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Moldova captain Alexandru
Curtianu, who plays for Zenit St Petersburg, remained in critical
condition with serious head injuries on Wednesday after being
attacked outside his apartment.
</P>
<P>
Zenit St Petersburg, the club for which Curtianu plays, said
the 25-year-old midfielder was struck on the head at the entrance
of his apartment building on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The incident was the latest in a series of attacks on high-
profile sports figures in Russian cities in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, a son of Rotor Volgograd's president was
beaten to death in a forest outside the southern city while Oleg
Veretennikov, Rotor's top scorer, and his two-year-old daughter
suffered face and hand burns after being sprayed with acid.
