<HEADLINE> Venezuelans Approve New Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's National Electoral
Council announced Wednesday night that the draft constitution was
approved by the majority of votes in a referendum.
</P>
<P>
Initial results showed that with about half the ballots counted,
71 percent voted in favor of the new constitution and 29 percent
were opposed.
</P>
<P>
Venezuelans voted under torrential rains Wednesday in a
referendum on the country's new constitution promoted by President
Hugo Chaves.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 11 million Venezuelans should vote Wednesday on a
proposed constitution that would transform the nation, changing
its name, eliminating the senate and giving President Hugo Chavez
the opportunity to stay in office for up to 13 years.
</P>
<P>
Chavez has made the 350-article draft-law the centerpiece of
his "peaceful revolution" against widespread corruption and
poverty in the world's third-largest oil exporter. 
</P>
